a64_hook - ARM64 Inline Hook Engine + GUI Framebuffer Overlay
=============================================================

ARM64 inline hook engine with a portable kernel-space GUI
framebuffer overlay for QEMU virtio-gpu on Android GKI kernels
(5.10-6.x). Uses runtime-only symbol resolution via /proc/kallsyms
— no DRM, no fbdev, no hardcoded addresses.

Hook Engine Features:
  - DMA physical memory writes (ioremap + memcpy_toio)
  - stop_machine atomic patching
  - Kprobe/kretprobe fallback
  - Hook chaining (multiple hooks per address)
  - BPF handler integration
  - Integrity checker (corruption detection + repair)
  - Perf monitoring (call count, cycle timing)
  - ARMv8.0-v8.6 decode (SVE, MTE, PAC, BTI, FP16)
  - 146/146 user-space tests passing

GUI Overlay (a64_hook_gui + a64_hook_win):
  - Markdown-style rendering in kernel space
  - Rectangles, text, colors (hex RGB)
  - Virtual window management with Z-ordering
  - virtio-gpu framebuffer backend (no DRM)
  - Procfs control: /proc/a64_hook_gui
  - Commands: clear, rect, text, fps, window, swap

Build:
  make KERNELDIR=/path/to/kernel/build/dir \
    ARCH=arm64 CROSS_COMPILE=aarch64-linux-gnu-

  Docker cross-build:
    ./scripts/build_docker.sh

QEMU Test:
  cd qemu_test/
  ./run.sh              # nographic test
  ./run.sh gui          # VNC mode (vnc://localhost:5900)

Install on Android:
  adb push a64_hook.ko /data/local/tmp/
  adb shell su -c "insmod /data/local/tmp/a64_hook.ko"

Verify:
  cat /proc/a64_hook
  cat /proc/a64_hook_gui

GUI Commands:
  echo "clear FF1A1A2E" > /proc/a64_hook_gui
  echo "rect 10 10 100 40 FF0F3460" > /proc/a64_hook_gui
  echo "text 20 20 FFFFFF 0F3460 Hello" > /proc/a64_hook_gui
  echo "window 0 10 10 200 100" > /proc/a64_hook_gui

API:
  See include/a64_hook.h for the full public API.
  GUI API: a64_gui_init(), a64_gui_command(), etc.

Status:
  146/146 user-space tests passing.
  Module init confirmed working on mainline 5.15.194.
  Requires matching kernel config for struct module layout.

